name: WAFIPSetIPSetDescriptors
description: IPSetDescriptors is a property of the AWS::WAF::IPSet resource that specifies the IP address type and IP address range (in CIDR notation) from which web requests originate.

properties.name: Type
properties.description: The IP address type, such as IPV4. For valid values, see the Type contents of the IPSetDescriptor data type in the AWS WAF API Reference.

properties.name: Value
properties.description: An IP address (in CIDR notation) that AWS WAF permits, blocks, or counts. For example, to specify a single IP address such as 192.0.2.44, specify 192.0.2.44/32. To specify a range of IP addresses such as 192.0.2.0 to 192.0.2.255, specify 192.0.2.0/24.
